# Role: content-moderation-engineer

> **Owns:** The content review workflow — list pending articles, approve, reject with feedback, reviewer dashboard.
> Do not create or modify files outside the Owned Paths below without a PR reviewed by someone currently holding this role.

## Role Charter
You make the Pending → Published/Rejected decision and record it. You do **not** own the rest of the article status machine (Draft → Pending, Rejected → Draft on edit) — that belongs to `content-authoring-engineer`; you call their `articleRepository.updateStatus()` method rather than duplicating the transition logic.

## Owned Paths
```
src/controllers/reviewerController.ts
src/services/reviewerService.ts
src/routes/reviewerRoutes.ts
src/app/(dashboard)/reviewer/approvals/page.tsx
src/components/reviewer/RejectModal.tsx
```

## Project Context
- Stack: Next.js + TypeScript (FE), Express + TypeScript (BE), Neon PostgreSQL
- Auth: import `authenticate` and `requireRole` from `authentication-engineer` / `authorization-engineer` — never rewrite them
- API prefix: `/api/v1/`

## Article Status Machine (context — you only own the Pending exit transitions)
```
     [Draft] ──submit──→ [Pending] ──approve──→ [Published]
       ↑                     |
       └──(author edits)─── reject ──→ [Rejected]
```

## Strict Rules
1. Only **Reviewer** or **Admin** can approve/reject.
2. Rejection **requires** feedback text — validate minimum 10 characters.
3. When an author edits a Rejected article, status automatically resets to Draft — that reset lives in `content-authoring-engineer`'s `ArticleService`; do not duplicate it here. Your `ReviewService` only handles `Pending → Published/Rejected`.
4. On approve: send notification to article author.
5. On reject: send notification to article author with the feedback text.
6. On submit (Pending): send notification to all users with Reviewer role.
7. To trigger any notification, call `notificationService.send()` / `sendToRole()` — do not implement notification storage yourself; that's `notification-engineer`'s.
8. Never touch article CRUD, article ownership checks, or the Draft/Pending/Rejected-on-edit transitions (`content-authoring-engineer`'s domain).

```typescript
// src/services/reviewerService.ts
async approveArticle(articleId: string, reviewId: string, reviewerId: string): Promise<Article> {
  const article = await articleRepository.findById(articleId);
  if (!article) throw new AppError('Article not found', 404);
  if (article.status !== 'Pending') {
    throw new AppError('Only Pending articles can be approved', 400);
  }

  const approved = await articleRepository.updateStatus(articleId, 'Published');

  notificationService.send({
    recipient_id: article.authorId,
    type: 'success',
    notification_reference_type: 'article',
    notification_title: 'Your review request has been approved',
    message: `Your article "${article.title}" has been approved and published!`,
    reference_id: articleId,
  }).catch(err => logger.error('Notification failed', { err }));

  return approved;
}

async rejectArticle(articleId: string, reviewId: string, reviewerId: string, feedback: string): Promise<Article> {
  if (!feedback || feedback.trim().length < 10) {
    throw new AppError('Rejection feedback must be at least 10 characters', 400);
  }

  const article = await articleRepository.findById(articleId);
  if (!article) throw new AppError('Article not found', 404);
  if (article.status !== 'Pending') {
    throw new AppError('Only Pending articles can be rejected', 400);
  }

  const rejected = await articleRepository.rejectWithFeedback(articleId, feedback);

  notificationService.send({
    recipient_id: article.authorId,
    type: 'failure',
    notification_reference_type: 'review',
    notification_title: 'Your review request has been rejected',
    message: `Your article "${article.title}" was rejected. Feedback: ${feedback}`,
    reference_id: reviewId,
  }).catch(err => logger.error('Notification failed', { err }));

  return rejected;
}
```

